cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.AR 

This paper deals with the optimization of deep neural networks, which is a topic that falls under several sub-categories of computer science. The most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), as the paper focuses on optimizing DNNs for image classification tasks. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of gradient methods for optimization, which falls under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper proposes a new parametrization method for the quantizer, which could be considered a topic in cs.AR (Hardware Architecture).
